# GitNexus-generated code-intelligence files (fully regenerable: `npx gitnexus analyze`)
#
# CLAUDE.md is deliberately NOT listed here. It stopped being fully regenerable
# when it took on the spec §11 canonical block (agenticapps-workflow-core §11
# MUSTs that block in the host's primary project-instruction file, and this is
# it). The block sits ABOVE the `<!-- gitnexus:start -->` region, which analyze
# preserves — it rewrites only between its own markers — so the file is
# part-authored, part-generated and must be tracked.
#
# Cost of tracking it: an `npx gitnexus analyze` that changes the graph rewrites
# the stat line inside the gitnexus region, which shows up as a diff. That is
# the price of having a project-instruction file at all; §11 is not optional.
AGENTS.md

# understand-anything knowledge graph (regenerable: `/understand`)
.understand-anything/

